# grapher_expr_scroll_smoke.numos — Phase 9E. Fill the expression list to MAX_FUNCS
# (6 implicit functions x, 2x, 3x, 4x, 5x, 6x) so it overflows the panel and must
# scroll, then exercise up/down navigation. Screenshot, assert. Proves the Phase 9E
# scroll-stability fixes (GrapherApp.cpp):
#   * refreshExprFocus() snaps the focused row into view (lv_obj_scroll_to_view,
#     LV_ANIM_OFF) so the selection never disappears below the fold;
#   * the _panelExpr lost SCROLL_MOMENTUM/ELASTIC, so there is no overscroll jitter;
#   * the "ENTER=edit" hint moved to the non-scrollable background as a fixed footer,
#     so it no longer scrolls on top of a row or clips the bottom.
# Final state: list scrolled to the bottom, slot 5 (y=6x) selected and fully visible,
# footer hint clean.
#
# Warning-only candidate (no golden blessed; the compare step warns when absent).
log "grapher_expr_scroll_smoke: waiting for launcher"
wait 200
open_app Grapher
wait 60
key down
key enter
key x
key enter
wait 16
key down
key enter
key 2
key x
key enter
wait 16
key down
key enter
key 3
key x
key enter
wait 16
key down
key enter
key 4
key x
key enter
wait 16
key down
key enter
key 5
key x
key enter
wait 16
key down
key enter
key 6
key x
key enter
wait 40
# Exercise up-scroll to the top then back down to the bottom (stability check).
key up
key up
key up
key up
key up
key up
wait 30
key down
key down
key down
key down
key down
wait 40
screenshot out/grapher_expr_scroll_smoke.ppm
assert_app Grapher
log "grapher_expr_scroll_smoke: 6-function list scrolled, selection visible, footer clean"
